			<abstract>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>In this paper we summarize our participation in the CLEF conference 2021 regarding the Profiling Hate Speech Spreaders on Twitter task. We suggested a Support Vector Machine classifier that uses as features word n-grams. Our final software achieved an accuracy of 72% in English, 82% in Spanish and therefore, an average accuracy of 77%.</p></div>
